<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 49/2000 amending Council Regulation (EC) No 1139/98 concerning the compulsory indication on the labelling of certain foodstuffs produced from genetically modified organisms of particulars other than those provided for in Directive 79/112/EEC </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 49/2000, millega muudetakse n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 1139/98 direktiivis 79/112/EM&Uuml; s&auml;testamata andmete kohustusliku lisamise kohta teatavate geneetiliselt muundatud organismidest toodetud toiduainete m&auml;rgistusele 10. jaanuar 2000 </eesti>
<inglise> of 10 January 2000 </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, Having regard to Council Directive 79/112/EEC of 18 December 1978 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to the labelling, presentation and advertising of foodstuffs(1), as last amended by Directive 97/4/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council(2), and in particular Article 4(2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 18. detsembri 1978. aasta direktiivi 79/112/EM&Uuml; toiduainete m&auml;rgistust, esitlemist ja reklaami k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta, (1) viimati muudetud Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu direktiiviga 97/4/E&Uuml;, (2) eriti selle artikli 4 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Council Regulation (EC) No 1139/98(3) laid down the compulsory indication on the labelling of foods and food ingredients produced from genetically modified soya (Glycine max L.) covered by Commission Decision 96/281/EC(4) and genetically modified maize (Zea mays L.) covered by Commission Decision 97/98/EC(5), of particulars other than those provided for in Directive 79/112/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rus (E&Uuml;) nr 1139/98 (3) n&auml;gi ette komisjoni otsusega 96/281/E&Uuml; (4) h&otilde;lmatud geneetiliselt muundatud sojaoast (Glycine max L.) ja komisjoni otsusega 97/98/E&Uuml; (5) h&otilde;lmatud geneetiliselt muundatud maisist (Zea mays L.) valmistatud toidu ja toidu koostisainete m&auml;rgistusele muude kohustuslike andmete lisamise peale direktiivis 79/112/EM&Uuml; s&auml;testatute; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Council Regulation (EC) No 1139/98 acknowledged that adventitious contamination of foodstuffs with DNA or protein resulting from genetic modification cannot be excluded; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rus (E&Uuml;) nr 1139/98 tunnistas, et ei saa v&auml;listada toiduainete juhuslikku saastumist geneetilisest muundamisest tuleneva DNA v&otilde;i valguga; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) consequently, the Council, at the moment of adopting Council Regulation (EC) No 1139/98, invited the Commission to study the practicality of setting up de minimis thresholds for the presence of DNA or protein resulting from genetic modification in order to take account of the problem of adventitious contamination; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) seet&otilde;ttu kutsus n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1139/98 vastuv&otilde;tmise ajal komisjoni &uuml;les uurima, kas on otstarbekas kehtestada geneetilisest muundamisest tuleneva DNA v&otilde;i valgu minimaalsed esinemisl&auml;ved, et v&otilde;tta arvesse juhusliku saastumise probleemi; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) despite the fact that some operators avoid using genetically modified soya beans (Glycine max L.) or maize (Zea mays L.) or produce thereof as a source for their food ingredients, material derived from the said genetically modified organisms may be present in them as a result of adventitious contamination during e.g., cultivation, harvest, transport, storage and processing; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) vaatamata t&otilde;siasjale, et m&otilde;ned ettev&otilde;tjad v&auml;ldivad geneetiliselt muundatud sojaoa (Glycine max L.) ja maisi (Zea mays L.) ning neist valmistatud toodete kasutamist toidu koostisainete allikana, v&otilde;ib neis esineda k&otilde;nealustest geneetiliselt muundatud organismidest p&auml;rit materjali n&auml;iteks k&uuml;lvi, koristuse, veo, ladustamise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise ajal toimunud juhusliku saastumise tulemusena; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) in the cases in which the presence of such material is adventitious and represents only a small proportion of a food ingredient considered, this food ingredient should not be subject to the labelling requirements of Regulation (EC) No 1139/98; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) juhtudel, mil sellise materjali esinemine on juhuslik ja moodustab vaadeldud toidu koostisainest &uuml;ksnes v&auml;ikese osa, ei tohiks m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1139/98 m&auml;rgistusn&otilde;uded k&otilde;nealuse toidu koostisaine suhtes kehtida; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) in order to achieve this objective, it is necessary to establish a de minimis threshold for the adventitious presence in food ingredients of material derived from the abovementioned genetically modified soya and maize; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks on vaja kehtestada miinimuml&auml;vi eespool nimetatud geneetiliselt muundatud sojaoast ja maisist saadud materjali juhusliku esinemise suhtes toidu koostisainetes; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) for the purpose of clarity, it is appropriate to fix a threshold in terms of a single percentage value; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) selguse m&otilde;ttes on kohane kinnitada l&auml;vi &uuml;htse protsendim&auml;&auml;rana; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) the value of 1 % best serves the purpose of establishing a tolerance level which simultaneously remains low and takes into account the necessary feasibility along the production chain. </inglise>
<eesti> 8) 1% sobib k&otilde;ige paremini lubatud tasemeks, mis on &uuml;htaegu madal ja v&otilde;tab arvesse vajalikku teostatavust tootmisahelas. </eesti>
<inglise> Detection methods already provide or shortly will, the necessary tools to implement this value. </inglise>
<eesti> Tuvastusmeetodid juba pakuvad v&otilde;i hakkavad peagi pakkuma vajalikke vahendeid selle m&auml;&auml;ra rakendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Nonetheless the 1 % value is to be seen as a maximum, and operators should therefore aim at achieving the lowest possible level of adventitious presence of the said material in practice; </inglise>
<eesti> Siiski tuleb 1%-list m&auml;&auml;ra lugeda maksimaalseks ning seet&otilde;ttu peaksid ettev&otilde;tjad seadma eesm&auml;rgiks saavutada praktikas k&otilde;nealuste ainete madalaim v&otilde;imalik tase; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) it is appropriate to clarify that the 1 % value should be the tolerance level not only for the adventitious presence of material derived from the abovementioned genetically modified organisms, but for the combined adventitious presence of such material and any other material placed on the market pursuant to Regulation (EC) No 258/97(6) derived from other genetically modified organisms; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) on kohane m&auml;rkida, et 1%-line m&auml;&auml;r peaks kujutama endast lubatud taset mitte &uuml;ksnes eespool nimetatud geneetiliselt muundatud organismidest saadud materjali juhuslikule esinemisele, vaid sellise materjali ja k&otilde;igi muude teistest geneetiliselt muundatud organismidest saadud ja m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 258/97 (6) alusel turule viidud materjalide juhuslikule esinemisele kokku; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) the notion of material derived from the genetically modified organisms should be understood as referring to the part of each ingredient that is derived from the genetically modified organisms; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) geneetiliselt muundatud organismidest saadud materjali m&otilde;istet tuleb m&otilde;ista viitena iga koostisaine sellisele osale, mis on saadud geneetiliselt muundatud organismidest; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) in order to establish that the presence of this material is adventitious, operators must be in a position to supply evidence to satisfy competent authorities that they have taken appropriate steps to avoid using as a source genetically modified soya beans (Glycine max L.) or maize (Zea mays L.), or any other additional genetically modified organisms whose derived material has been placed on the market pursuant to Regulation (EC) No 258/97, or produce thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) selleks, et teha kindlaks, kas nimetatud materjali esinemine on juhuslik, peavad ettev&otilde;tjad suutma esitada p&auml;devaid asutusi rahuldavad t&otilde;endid selle kohta, et nad on v&otilde;tnud vajalikke meetmeid, et v&auml;ltida geneetiliselt muundatud sojaoa (Glycine max L.), maisi (Zea mays L.) v&otilde;i muudest t&auml;iendavatest geneetiliselt muundatud organismidest saadud ja m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 258/97 alusel turule viidud materjali v&otilde;i nendest saadud toodete kasutamist l&auml;hteainena; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) for the purposes of consistency with Directive 79/112/EEC, it is appropriate to apply the threshold at the level of food ingredients individually considered; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) selleks et tagada j&auml;rjepidevus direktiivi 79/112/EM&Uuml; suhtes, on vaja kohaldada l&auml;ve iga &uuml;ksiku toidu koostisaine suhtes eraldi; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) it should be clarified that the same approach is to be followed for the purpose of establishing a list of food ingredients not subject to the labelling requirements of Regulation (EC) No 1139/98 because of the absence of protein and DNA resulting from the genetic modification as specified in its Article 1(1); </inglise>
<eesti> 13) tuleb m&auml;rkida, et sama l&auml;henemisviisi tuleb kasutada selliste toidu koostisainete nimekirja koostamisel, mille suhtes m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1139/98 m&auml;rgistusn&otilde;uded selle artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud geneetilisest muundamisest tulenevate valkude ja DNA puudumise t&otilde;ttu ei kehti; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) in any case, food ingredients are not subject to the labelling requirements of Regulation (EC) No 1139/98 when neither protein nor DNA resulting from the genetic modification as specified in Article 1(1) is present. </inglise>
<eesti> 14) igal juhul ei kehti toidu koostisainete suhtes m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1138/98 m&auml;rgistusn&otilde;uded siis, kui neis ei esine nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud geneetilisest muundamisest tulenevat valku ega DNAd. </eesti>
<inglise> In this light, it is appropriate to clarify that such list is not exhaustive; </inglise>
<eesti> Seda silmas pidades on kohane m&auml;rkida, et niisugune nimekiri ei ole ammendav; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) in some cases foods comprise a single ingredient. </inglise>
<eesti> 15) m&otilde;nedel juhtudel koosnevad toidud &uuml;hestainsast koostisainest. </eesti>
<inglise> It is therefore necessary to bring clarity as to how these foods should be considered for the purposes of establishing the abovementioned list and for the application of the threshold; </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu on vaja teha selgeks, kuidas neid toite eespool nimetatud nimekirja koostamise ja l&auml;ve kohaldamise seisukohalt k&auml;sitada; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) Directive 79/112/EEC applies to products which are delivered as such not only to the ultimate consumer, but also to mass caterers; </inglise>
<eesti> 16) direktiivi 79/112/EM&Uuml; kohaldatakse toodete suhtes, mida tarnitakse sellistena mitte &uuml;ksnes l&otilde;pptarbijale, vaid ka toitlustusettev&otilde;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise> (17) the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Committee for foodstuffs, </inglise>
<eesti> 17) k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses ette n&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las alalise toiduainekomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EC) No 1139/98 is modified as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1139/98 muudetakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In Article 1(1), "to the final consumer" is replaced by "to the final consumer or mass caterers". </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 asendatakse s&otilde;na "l&otilde;pptarbijale" s&otilde;nadega "l&otilde;pptarbijale v&otilde;i toitlustusettev&otilde;tetele". </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 is modified as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklit 2 muudetakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) Paragraph 2 is replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> a) l&otilde;ige 2 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "2. </inglise>
<eesti> "2. </eesti>
<inglise> The specified foodstuffs shall not be subject to the additional specific labelling requirements where: </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud toiduainete suhtes ei kehti t&auml;iendavad m&auml;rgistuse erin&otilde;uded, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) neither protein nor DNA resulting from genetic modification as specified in Article 1(1) is present in their food ingredients individually considered or the food comprising a single ingredient; </inglise>
<eesti> a) nende toidu koostisainetes &uuml;ksikult v&otilde;etuna ega &uuml;hest koostisainest koosnevas toidus ei esine artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud geneetilisest muundamisest tulenevat valku ega DNAd; </eesti>
<inglise> or </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (b) material derived from the genetically modified organisms referred to in Article 1(1), together with any material placed on the market pursuant to Regulation (EC) No 258/97 derived from other genetically modified organisms, is present in their food ingredients or the food comprising a single ingredient in a proportion no higher than 1 % of the food ingredients individually considered or food comprising a single ingredient, provided this presence is adventitious; </inglise>
<eesti> b) artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud geneetiliselt muundatud organismidest saadud materjal koos muudest geneetiliselt muundatud organismidest saadud materjaliga, mis on m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 258/97 alusel turule viidud, esineb toidu koostisainetes v&otilde;i &uuml;hest koostisainest koosnevas toidus k&otilde;ige rohkem 1% ulatuses toidu koostisainetest &uuml;kshaaval v&otilde;etuna v&otilde;i &uuml;hest koostisainest koosnevast toidust, tingimusel, et see materjal esineb seal juhuslikult. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to establish that the presence of this material is adventitious, operators must be in a position to supply evidence to satisfy the competent authorities that they have taken appropriate steps to avoid using the genetically modified organisms (or produce thereof) referred to in the previous paragraph as a source." </inglise>
<eesti> Tuvastamaks, et nimetatud materjali esinemine on juhuslik, peavad ettev&otilde;tjad suutma esitada p&auml;devaid asutusi rahuldavad t&otilde;endid selle kohta, et nad on v&otilde;tnud vajalikke meetmeid, et v&auml;ltida eelmises l&otilde;ikes osutatud geneetiliselt muundatud organismide (v&otilde;i nendest saadud toodete) kasutamist l&auml;hteainena." </eesti>
<inglise> (b) The following paragraph 2a is inserted: </inglise>
<eesti> b) Lisatakse l&otilde;ige 2a: </eesti>
<inglise> "2a. </inglise>
<eesti> "2a. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to facilitate the application of paragraph 2(a), a non-exhaustive list of food ingredients or foods comprising a single ingredient in which neither protein nor DNA resulting from the genetic modification as specified in Article 1(1) is present, shall be drawn up under the procedure laid down in Article 17 of Directive 79/112/EEC, taking account of technical developments, the opinion of the Scientific Committee for food and any other relevant scientific advice." </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks, et h&otilde;lbustada l&otilde;ike 2 punkti a kohaldamist, koostatakse direktiivi 79/112/EM&Uuml; artiklis 17 s&auml;testatud korras mittet&auml;ielik nimekiri toidu koostisainetest ja &uuml;hest koostisainest koosnevatest toitudest, kus ei esine artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud geneetilisest muundamisest tulenevat valku ega DNAd, v&otilde;ttes arvesse tehnika arengut, toitluse teaduskomitee arvamust ja k&otilde;iki muid asjakohaseid teaduslikke n&otilde;uandeid." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The labelling requirements of Regulation (EC) No 1139/98 shall not apply to specified foodstuffs which are to be delivered as such to mass caterers which have been lawfully manufactured and labelled in the Community, or which have been lawfully imported into the Community and put into free circulation, before the entry into force of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1139/98 m&auml;rgistusn&otilde;udeid ei kohaldata kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud toiduainete suhtes, mida tarnitakse sellistena toitlustusettev&otilde;tetele ning mis on enne k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumist &uuml;henduses seaduslikult valmistatud ja m&auml;rgistatud v&otilde;i seaduslikult &uuml;hendusse imporditud ja vabasse ringlusse lastud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the ninetieth day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub &uuml;heksak&uuml;mnendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 10 January 2000. </inglise>
